1. CSS Font Properties (Typography Layouts)When you write standard HTML, text renders with a baseline styling native to the browser [02:22]. You can control its core attributes using these key CSS properties:font-style: Changes the look of your text block. Setting it to italic shifts characters into stylized diagonal paths [03:09].font-size: Adjusts the scale of your text (e.g., font-size: 20px;) [03:40].What is a Pixel (px)? Just like kilometers track distance, pixels act as spatial scaling benchmarks on screens [04:34]. A single physical layout pixel evaluates strictly to $1/96 \text{ of an inch}$ (approx. $0.26 \text{ mm}$) [05:06].font-weight: Governs line thickness and visual density. Values range from lightweight to thick bold formats (100 is thin/light, while 900 forces thick black bold shapes) [07:17].line-height: Controls vertical separation between sequential rows of text. Setting a higher value (like 90px) expands text separation to clean up compact page blocks [08:24].2. Font Families and FallbacksCSSp {
  font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
}
Web Safe Fonts: Standard pre-installed fonts (like Arial or Times New Roman) that are guaranteed to exist natively across almost all universal devices and browsers [11:15].Fall-back System: When you chain multiple choices separated by commas, it creates a priority queue [10:41]. If the browser cannot load choice 1 due to OS differences, it falls back to choice 2, and eventually sinks into a generic catch-all design system category like serif or sans-serif [10:54].Integrating External Custom Google FontsIf you want a modern font style that isn't pre-installed on devices, you can pull it from Google Fonts [11:34]:Find your preferred font selection on Google Fonts and click the selection trigger button [11:44].Copy the generated external <link> definitions block and embed it directly into your layout's HTML <head> tag [12:17].Apply the custom family string right into your active CSS stylesheet sheet rules [12:36]:HTML<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Caveat&display=swap">

<style>
  p { font-family: 'Caveat', cursive; }
</style>
3. Four Methods to Define Colors in CSSYou can declare background colors or text typography color properties using four distinct models [14:32]:MethodSyntax ExampleBehavioral BreakdownNamed Colorscolor: brown;Simplest approach using clear pre-programmed dictionary names (e.g., yellow, blue) [15:43].RGB Functioncolor: rgb(100, 109, 192);Combines Red, Green, and Blue sub-channels on a scale from 0 to 255 [16:56].RGBA Variantcolor: rgba(0, 200, 0, 0.5);Adds a fourth Alpha value (0.0 to 1.0) to explicitly set opacity levels ($0 = \text{invisible}$, $1 = \text{solid}$) [18:03].Hexadecimalcolor: #67BBB1;A base-16 tracking format prefixed with # [19:51]. Hex characters split linearly into thematic segments representing #RRGGBB (and optionally #RRGGBBAA for opacity layers) [20:49].HSL Systemcolor: hsl(120, 100%, 50%);H (Hue): Value on a $0^{\circ} \text{--} 360^{\circ}$ circular color wheel ($0^{\circ}=\text{red}$, $120^{\circ}=\text{green}$, $240^{\circ}=\text{blue}$) [23:20].S (Saturation): Color intensity level ($0\%=\text{gray}$, $100\%=\text{vibrant}$) [23:32].L (Lightness): Total white/black balance level ($0\%=\text{pitch black}$, $100\%=\text{stark white}$) [23:51].4. Leveraging Browser Developer ToolsBy hitting Right-Click $\rightarrow$ Inspect Element, you gain deep real-time insights into your page's document structure [28:01]:The Elements Tab: Lets you trace your markup live. Hovering over a line of code highlights its physical spacing limits inside the viewport window [29:28].The Styles Sub-Panel: Displays every CSS rule currently targeting an element [29:53]. You can uncheck properties or swap custom color palette declarations to test edits instantly on your screen [30:06].User Agent Stylesheets: Default baseline styling settings automatically injected by your browser (like native heading sizing or margin spaces) that you can cleanly override with your custom CSS sheets [32:07].⚠️ The Sandbox Rule: Modifying markup text properties or forcing background overrides directly inside DevTools changes things only within your local browser memory window sandbox [31:05]. If you reload the page tab, it completely resets back to its true repository code baseline files [31:21].